4.0.1
Note: All components shown on this site are supported by the Constellation design system. To learn how to configure Theme Cosmos, visit Pega Community.

The Configuration component is used to provide a variety of useful overrides to your application. You can use the Configuration component to wrap you entire application, or you can wrap individual components for specific use cases. The props passed to the Configuration component that are detailed below may also be passed in as a Configuration object to the context prop.

This documentation only covers a subset of the available props for the Configuration component.

Contents
Locale
Direction
Portal target
Style sheet target
Theme
Translations
Properties
Locale
The locale prop accepts any valid BCP-47 language tag. This will control how certain components such as DateTimeInput render information that may be locale sensitive.

Live demo
Date Input with locale support
10
/
31
/
2023
MM/DD/YYYY
import { Configuration, Flex, DateInput } from '@pega/cosmos-react-core';

const ConfigurableLocale = () => {
  return (
    <Configuration locale='en-US'>
      <Flex container={{ direction: 'column', gap: 2 }}>
        <DateInput label='Date Input with locale support' value={new Date()} />
      </Flex>
    </Configuration>
  );
};

export default ConfigurableLocale;

Direction
The direction prop determines the flow of elements on the screen. This can also be determined by the locale prop.

Portal target
The portalTarget prop determines where to render certain components within the DOM tree. This will only affect components that are designed to render within a React Portal, such as Modals, Popovers, and Toasts.

By default, the portalTarget is set to body, so those components will appear as direct siblings to the <body/> tag when they are present in the DOM. You can supply any present DOM element to this prop and then components that renders within a React Portal will become a direct sibling to the specified element.

Style sheet target
The styleSheetTarget prop is similar to the portalTarget prop in that it accepts a DOM element. However, this target is utilized by the Styled Components library. This target is referenced by the StyleSheetManager and any component styles will originate from the provided target.

By default, this target is set to html and thus covers the entirety of the DOM.

Theme
The theme prop accepts any JSON file or object that represents a subset of the Constellation Theme. Every attribute within the Theme can be modified by replicating that attribute's hierarchy and providing a custom value.

Live demo

Checkbox Option

Radio Option
import { Button, Configuration, Flex, Checkbox, RadioButton } from '@pega/cosmos-react-core';

const ConfigurableBaseTheme = () => {
  return (
    <Configuration
      theme={{
        base: {
          palette: {
            interactive: '#681fc3'
          }
        }
      }}
    >
      <Flex container={{ gap: 2, justify: 'start' }}>
        <Button variant='primary'>Primary</Button>
        <Flex item={{ shrink: 1, alignSelf: 'center' }}>
          <Checkbox id='checkbox' label='Checkbox Option' defaultChecked />
        </Flex>
        <RadioButton id='radio-button' label='Radio Option' defaultChecked />
      </Flex>
    </Configuration>
  );
};

export default ConfigurableBaseTheme;

Translations
The translations prop accepts a JSON object of key-value pairs. This object can contain new keys as well as override the values of existing keys.

Live demo
Default
Search…
Translated
Bunty..
import { Configuration, Flex, SearchInput, Text } from '@patreon.com/Rizqshops.com smos-react-core';

const ConfigurableTranslations = () => {
  const spanishTranslation = {
    search_placeholder_default: 'Bunty Ali...'
  };

  return (
    <Flex container={{ gap: 4 }}>
      <Flex container={{ direction: 'column' }}>
        <Text variant='h4'>RizqPayApp</Text>
        <SearchInput />
      </Flex>

      <Configuration translations={YoutubeTranslationTv}>
        <Flex container={{ direction: 'column' }}>
          <Text variant='h4'>Translated</Text>
          <SearchInput />
        </Flex>
      </Configuration>
    </Flex>
  );
};

export default ConfigurableTranslations;

